Bio::GeneDesign

ABOUT

It's about synthetic biology - specifically, designing constructs up to 10kb in
size.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	
Answer the following questions (may differ based on your system, [defaults]):

			Where should GeneDesign write tmp files? [ /tmp ]
			Where should GeneDesign config files be installed? [ /etc/GeneDesign/ ]
			Should GeneDesign install scripts? [ Y ]
			Where should GeneDesign scripts be installed? [ /usr/local/bin/ ]
			Enable GD::Graphics support? [ Y ]

You may need to install some additional perl modules for it to work:

	./Build installdeps
	
Then run the following:

	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

Then enjoy GeneDesign.


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Bio::GeneDesign

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Bio::GeneDesign

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Bio::GeneDesign

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Bio::GeneDesign

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Bio::GeneDesign/

